Gunmen at about 8am on Sunday kidnapped one Mr. Patrick Kogbodi, proprietor of Kogbodi International School in Ughelli, Delta State. The gunmen waylaid the victim’s vehicle and whisked him to unknown destination. The Delta State Police Commissioner, CP Adeyinka Adeleke, in a telephone chat with DAILY POST, confirmed the incident.
CP Adeyinka said, “It is true. The incident happened when the man was going to church in Ughelli this morning.” Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.